{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, the LLM places the ground-truth item \"Dick\" at the bottom of the ranking list.",
    "The possible reason is that relying solely on the movie title \"Dick\", LLMs cannot infer that the movie is a comedy film about two teenage girls, which has a greater similarity to the recently watched movie \"Showgirls\" by users.",
    "This case demonstrates that LLMs may make inappropriate decisions due to a lack of domain knowledge in the field of recommender systems.",
    "(b) Case study of the lack of domain knowledge when leveraging GPT-4 [99] as the zero-shot re-ranker on the MovieLens-1M dataset.",
    "\"Dick\" is a comedy film about two teenager girls, which is relevant to the movie \"Showgirls\", but GPT-4 ranks \"Dick\" at the end of the list."
  ]
}